<Docs title="Get Working Fast" description="Choose the shortest provider path to a working Omegon setup.">
  <h1>Get Working Fast</h1>
  <p>
    This section is for first successful setup, not a tour of Omegon internals. Pick the path
    that matches what you already have, follow the steps exactly, and confirm the success signal
    before exploring deeper features.
  </p>

  <h2>Choose Your Path</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Path</th><th>Best For</th><th>What You Need</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><a href="/docs/quickstart">OpenAI/Codex OAuth</a></td><td>Fastest default route for most operators</td><td>ChatGPT/Codex account and browser login</td></tr>
      <tr><td><a href="/docs/get-started/claude">Claude subscription</a></td><td>Interactive Claude-backed TUI work</td><td>Claude Pro/Max account and browser login</td></tr>
      <tr><td><a href="/docs/get-started/api-key">API key path</a></td><td>Direct control over provider credentials</td><td>At least one inference API key</td></tr>
      <tr><td><a href="/docs/get-started/ollama">Local Ollama path</a></td><td>Local/offline-first evaluation</td><td>Ollama installed and at least one model pulled</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <!-- DIAGRAM:provider-path-decision | Decision tree: "Have ChatGPT/Codex login?" → yes: OpenAI/Codex OAuth path | no → "Have Claude Pro/Max?" → Claude subscription path | no → "Have an API key?" → API key path | no → "Want offline?" → Ollama path -->

  <h2>What counts as success?</h2>
  <p>You are done with onboarding when all of these are true:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Omegon launches without provider/auth errors</li>
    <li>Your first prompt gets a real model response</li>
    <li>You see at least one tool call or file read in the conversation</li>
    <li>You know which path to revisit if setup breaks later</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>If a path fails</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Use the matching guide’s troubleshooting section first</li>
    <li>If the guide is wrong or incomplete, file a <strong>Setup problem</strong> issue</li>
    <li>If your real goal does not fit any path, file a <strong>Use case</strong> issue</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Prefer examples over theory at this stage. If you want a guided tour of the interface and
    Omegon’s internal model, use <a href="/docs/tutorial">/tutorial</a> afterward.
  </p>
</Docs>
